<TITLE> Court orders freezes on former MP MAH Selim's bank accounts </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 27 (bdnews24.com) -- A Dhaka court Thursday ordered 10 bank accounts belonging to former BNP lawmaker MAH Selim to be frozen. The former MP is accused of concealing information on the extent of his property and illegally amassing wealth. Additional chief metropolitan magistrate for Dhaka Md Golam RabbanI made the ruling following an appeal from the Anticorruption Commission. According to case details, the former MP, wife Amina Begum and their son Mehdi Hasan and daughter Sahara Selim amassed property worth Tk 62.95 crore through undeclared sources. In addition, they allegedly concealed information on property worth Tk 12.37 crore in the wealth statement submitted to the ACC. bdnew
